Privacy Policy.
Last updated: 27 Augest 2024.
1. Introduction
Welcome to Logo Maker! This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, disclose, and safeguard your personal information when you use our iOS app. By using our app, you agree to the practices described in this Privacy Policy.
2. Information We Collect
2.1 Personal Information.
We may collect the following personal information when you use our app:
- Your name and contact information (such as email address) when you voluntarily provide it.
- Your name, email address, profile photo, and third-party ID (e.g., Google, Facebook ID) when you sign up using Apple, Facebook, Google, or our app's login feature.
- User-generated content, such as logos and designs created using our app.
- Usage and device information in third parties for Analytics.
2.2 Non-Personal Information
We may also collect non-personal information, such as anonymized usage statistics and data that do not directly identify you.
3. How We Use Your Information
We use your personal information for the following purposes:
- To provide and improve our logo maker services.
- To communicate with you, respond to inquiries, and provide customer support.
- To send you updates, newsletters, and marketing materials (if you have opted in).
- To analyze app usage and trends to enhance user experience, including device name and version used by third-party services for performance improvement and crash analytics.
- To comply with legal obligations and protect our rights.
4. Data Security
We take reasonable steps to protect your personal information from unauthorized access or disclosure. However, no data transmission over the internet can be guaranteed as 100% secure, so we cannot ensure the absolute security of your information.
5. Data Deletion
To delete your data, navigate to the app's settings, go to the profile screen, and select "Delete Account." This action will permanently delete all your data from our app and server, including your name, email, and saved projects/drafts. If you have not signed up within the app, simply deleting the app will remove all locally stored data, including photos, videos, and saved templates.
6. Third-Party Services
Our app may contain links to third-party websites or services. We are not responsible for the privacy practices of these third parties, and we encourage you to review their privacy policies.
7. Children's Privacy
Our app is not intended for use by individuals under the age of 13. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children under 13. If you are a parent or guardian and believe we have collected information about your child, please contact us, and we will promptly delete the information. For social media logins, please note that they have their own age restrictions, typically requiring users to be at least 18 years old.
8. Changes to This Privacy Policy
We reserve the right to update this Privacy Policy to reflect changes in our practices and legal requirements. We will notify you of any material changes by posting the updated Privacy Policy within the app.
9. Contact Us
If you have any questions or concerns about our Privacy Policy, please contact us at:
appdev350@protool.app